               <msContents>
                  <summary>Papyrus draft of an official letter from the Arsinoites (modern name: Fayyum), Egypt. Concerns trouble caused by proselytes or newcomers who claimed the same tax privileges for their land as long-time residents. Mentions a village chief and village elders. Verso has another draft of an official letter in Greek (P.Duk.inv. 727 V)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Actual dimensions of item are 14.3 x 16.5 cm</note>
                     <note type="general">13 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">Written along the fibers on the recto; written across the fibers on the verso inverse to the text on the recto</note>
                     <note type="general">Left margin of 1.5 cm.; small right margin</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 727 R was formerly P.Duk.inv. MF79 76 R</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
